Count Two: Enticement to Engage in Illegal Sexual Activity - Second Element
The second element of Count Two which the government must prove beyond a reasonable doubt is that the individual[Jane Doe-1 pseudonym] traveled in interstate commerce from Florida to New York, as alleged in the Indictment.
As I just stated, "interstate commerce" simply means movement between one state and another.
Adapted from Sand et al., Modern Federal Jury Instructions, Instr. 64-8.
